# Environment variables

## Local dev (Docker Postgres)

Copy into `.env.local` (gitignored):

```bash
cp env.example .env.local
```

```bash
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://belong:belong@localhost:5433/belong
```

## Aurora production (IAM auth)

Copy into `.env.aurora` (gitignored):

```bash
cp env.aurora.example .env.aurora
```

Fill in `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` and `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` from the `belong-vercel` IAM user.
See `docs/deploy-production.md` for the full setup.

```bash
npm run db:migrate:iam
npm run db:seed:iam
```

Optional: run the app locally against Aurora by keeping `DATABASE_URL` out of `.env.local`
so `instrumentation.ts` loads `.env.aurora` automatically.

Optional for production cookies (generate a random string):

```bash
# SESSION_SECRET=your-random-secret-here
```
